==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moesogothic
<hw>Moe`so*goth"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Belonging to
the Moesogoths, a branch of the Goths who settled in Moesia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moesogothic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moesogothic
<hw>Moe`so*goth"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The language of the
Moesogoths; -- also called <altname>Gothic</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moeve</ent>⟦br⟧
